searchData={"content_type":"text/markdown","items":[{"doc":"","ref":"CsvSigil.html","title":"CsvSigil","type":"module"},{"doc":"Implement the `~v` sigil, which takes a string containing\nmultiple comma-separated lines, converts each line into a list,\nand returns a list of those lists.\nNumeric numbers are converted into float numbers.\n\nWith an `h` option, the sigil returns a list of keyword lists.\nThe keys in each keyword list is taken from the first line.\n(See the second example below.)","ref":"CsvSigil.html#sigil_v/2","title":"CsvSigil.sigil_v/2","type":"function"},{"doc":"```\n  iex> import CsvSigil\n  iex> ~v\"\"\"\n  ...> 1,2,3\n  ...> cat,dog\n  ...> \"\"\"\n  [[1.0, 2.0, 3.0], [\"cat\", \"dog\"]]\n\n  iex> import CsvSigil\n  iex> ~v\"\"\"\n  ...> Item,Qty,Price\n  ...> Teddy bear,4,34.95\n  ...> Milk,1,2.99\n  ...> Battery,6,8.00\n  ...> \"\"\"h\n  [\n    [Item: \"Teddy bear\", Qty: 4.0, Price: 34.95],\n    [Item: \"Milk\", Qty: 1.0, Price: 2.99],\n    [Item: \"Battery\", Qty: 6.0, Price: 8.00]\n  ]\n  ```","ref":"CsvSigil.html#sigil_v/2-example-usage","title":"Example usage - CsvSigil.sigil_v/2","type":"function"}]}